<h1 class="purposeless">Respre</h1>
<span class="dateline">October 24, 2014</span>

<section class="body">
	<p>
		This past weekend, I spent a few hours creating a little tool for responsive design. So little, in fact, that I think it can fit into most people’s responsive design workflows. It’s called <a href="http://github.com/aarongrando/respre">Respre</a> (short for <em>responsive preview</em>). <strong>Respre helps teams preview responsive web designs in-browser without writing any code.</strong>
	</p>
